{
  "stem": "22237.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You would go-- even not talking about school, even if you go-- went to any public place, like the post office, or the-- anyplace, you would see these banners that said-- [SPEAKING GERMAN] 'The Jews are our misfortune.' We had never seen that before.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And let me talk a little bit about the time before Hitler came on power.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was just the year-- in 1932-- I remember that my parents started getting quite worried because of his campaigning.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was campaigning.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was depression time, and he was campaigning and talking-- saying to the people that all we have to do to have a better life is to get rid of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That, of course-- and I remember myself, that was very depressing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my parents were worried but not really that concerned, because they always used to say-- my father used to call him 'clown' in-- in German.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He used to call him the-- the [GERMAN], which is a clown.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were concerned, but not terribly worried, because nobody would think this-- the Germans, this-- the Germans, who had the best scientists, the best doctors, the greatest authors in the world, that they would allow to-- for Hitler to get on power.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "However, in 1933, we were-- it was like waking up one morning, and he was the leader.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He became the leader like, overnight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And from then on, they got a little bit more concerned.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Not terribly concerned, but a little bit more concerned.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They just thought that somehow he would-- he would not last.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In some way, he couldn't last.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "However, he lasted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so after 1933, as-- as soon as he came on power, things had gotten bad.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because there was-- I used to have friends, Christian friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
